===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*kʷ-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|how}}, {{m|enm|hou}}, {{m|enm|hu}}, {{m|enm|hwu}}, from {{inh|en|ang|hū}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*hwō}}, from the same root as {{m|ang|hwæt||who, what}}. /hw/ > /h/ due to [[w:Wh-cluster reductions|''wh''-cluster reduction]] in Old English; compare {{m|en|who}}, which underwent this change later, and thus is spelt ''wh'' (Middle English spelling of /hw/) but pronounced /h/ (it previously had a different vowel, hence avoided the spelling and sound change in Old English). Vowel change per [[Great Vowel Shift]].

Akin to {{cog|sco|hoo}}, {{m|sco|foo||how}}, {{cog|stq|wo||how}}, {{cog|fy|hoe||how}}, {{cog|nds|ho}}, {{m|nds|wo}}, {{m|nds|wu||how}}, {{cog|nl|hoe||how}}, {{cog|de|wie||how}}, {{cog|sv|hur||how}}. See {{m|en|who}} and compare {{m|en|why}}.

